<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: The line box height is determined by content height.</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#line-height" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="The height of each inline box in the line box is calculated and the 'line-height' property." />
        <style>
            .c1
            {
                vertical-align: top;
                background: green;
            }
            div
            {
                border: solid 5px black;
                width: 96px;
                background: green;
            }
            #s1
            {
                font-size: 32pt;
                background: yellow;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the number "1" is contained within the yellow area and does not overflow the black borders while "Filler Text" appears contained and at the top/left of its green area.</p>
        <div>
            <span class="c1"><span id="s1">1</span><span class="c1">Filler Text</span></span>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>